This paper discusses bug bounty programs, which are related to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The study also involves strategic interactions among managers and participants, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the incentives and motivations of security researchers, which could be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybercrime (cs.CY).
